I need to fix TypeScript errors in 10 story files. The issue is that chart components have complex generic types, so `Meta<typeof Component>` produces `never` for args, causing "Property 'args' is missing" errors on stories that only use `render`.

The fix: In each story file, change the meta type pattern from:
```tsx
const meta = {
  component: SomeChart,
} satisfies Meta<typeof SomeChart>;

export default meta;
type Story = StoryObj<typeof meta>;
```

To:
```tsx
const meta: Meta = {
  component: SomeChart,
};

export default meta;
type Story = StoryObj<typeof meta>;
```

This uses the unparameterized `Meta` type which doesn't enforce args.

Apply this fix to all 10 files in /Users/kasperpeulen/code/storybook/storybook-eval/trials/2026-04-03T11-41-23Z-dda9c538/project/src/:
